# The provenance ledgers are append-only JSONL: every contributor's PR adds rows at
# the end, so two PRs in flight always "conflict" on the final line even though the
# right resolution is simply to keep both sets of rows. `merge=union` makes git take
# both sides' lines instead of raising a conflict, which is exactly correct for an
# append-only log and stops concurrent match PRs from blocking each other.
#
# Order within the file stops being meaningful under union merge, but nothing depends
# on it: both stores are keyed by id and read into a dict (last write wins), and the
# CI stamper dedupes by content before appending. A duplicate row from two sides
# stamping the same landing is harmless.
config/match_provenance.jsonl merge=union
config/match_attempts.jsonl   merge=union

# nearmiss/db.jsonl is NOT union-merged on purpose: it is one row per function keyed
# by (module, addr), and a union of two edits to the same function would leave two
# rows for it with different divergence counts. That needs the real line-union check
# the PR review already does, not a blind concatenation.
